8
00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:24.200
Excuse me.

9
00:01:24.360 --> 00:01:28.520
The bus to Cortland.
-What about her?

10
00:01:28.680 --> 00:01:34.000
Well. it was due a half an hour ago.
-Yup. half hour ago.

11
00:01:34.160 --> 00:01:38.320
When will it be in?
-Hard to say. Been raining hard.

12
00:01:38.480 --> 00:01:41.760
Road's slick. 
Maybe a bridge or two out.

13
00:01:41.920 --> 00:01:44.560
That'll play hard with the schedule.

14
00:01:44.720 --> 00:01:49.280
When do you think it will be in?

15
00:01:49.440 --> 00:01:52.280
She'll be in when she'll be in.
That's all.

16
00:01:52.440 --> 00:01:56.480
I told you that the last 
time you asked.

17
00:01:56.640 --> 00:02:01.120
The last time I asked was now. All
I want from you is a civil answer.

18
00:02:01.280 --> 00:02:02.800
You're getting a civil answer.

19
00:02:02.960 --> 00:02:05.960
The trouble is every ten minutes 
you're up here requiring one.

20
00:02:06.120 --> 00:02:09.320
Situations just don't 
change that rapidly.

21
00:02:09.480 --> 00:02:12.880
And you want to know about
the Cortland bus.

22
00:02:13.040 --> 00:02:15.520
It was late when you asked
a half hour ago.

23
00:02:15.680 --> 00:02:19.000
Late when you come back 15 
minutes later. And it's late now.

24
00:02:19.160 --> 00:02:23.120
And all the asking in the world
ain't going to push it none.

25
00:02:23.280 --> 00:02:27.680
But this is the very first time
I've been up here.

26
00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:32.160
Either you need your eyes...

27
00:02:44.080 --> 00:02:46.920
Now what's the matter?

28
00:02:47.080 --> 00:02:51.040
Nothing.

29
00:02:51.320 --> 00:02:55.360
Nothing's the matter.

30
00:02:59.520 --> 00:03:01.680
Millicent Barnes. age 25.

31
00:03:01.840 --> 00:03:05.000
Young woman waiting for a bus.

32
00:03:05.160 --> 00:03:07.680
Not a very imaginative type
is Ms Barnes.

33
00:03:07.840 --> 00:03:12.960
Not given to undue anxiety of fears
or temporal flights of fancy.

34
00:03:13.120 --> 00:03:17.080
Like most young career women.
she has a generic classification...

35
00:03:17.240 --> 00:03:20.600
as a 'Girl with a head 
on her shoulders.'

36
00:03:20.760 --> 00:03:23.680
All of which is mentioned now
because in just a moment...

37
00:03:23.800 --> 00:03:27.400
the head on Ms Barnes's shoulders
will be put to a test.

38
00:03:27.560 --> 00:03:31.560
Circumstances will assault 
her sense of reality...

39
00:03:31.720 --> 00:03:34.160
will put her sanity on a block.

40
00:03:34.320 --> 00:03:41.400
Millicent Barnes. who in one minute
will wonder if she's going mad.

41
00:04:04.880 --> 00:04:07.800
Shall we run through it again. miss?

42
00:04:07.960 --> 00:04:16.080
No. I was just saw. but that bag...
-What about it?

43
00:04:16.240 --> 00:04:20.480
It's just like mine. It's identical.
even to the broken handle.

44
00:04:20.640 --> 00:04:23.840
Is this. some kind of a game?
-What?

45
00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:26.080
That is your bag. You checked it.

46
00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:30.360
No. it looks just like my bag. 
but...

47
00:04:34.640 --> 00:04:37.120
Will you go over there and sit down?

48
00:04:37.280 --> 00:04:41.080
You're either walking in your sleep
or hung over or something.

49
00:04:41.240 --> 00:04:46.120
Go back and sit down. breathe 
through your nose and let me read.

50
00:04:46.280 --> 00:04:50.360
When the Cortland bus comes there'll
be a loud sound of an engine...

51
00:04:50.520 --> 00:04:54.080
a door opening. 
people will come in here.

52
00:04:54.240 --> 00:04:59.160
Then you'll know the bus is here.
-But I didn't check my bag.

53
00:04:59.320 --> 00:05:05.600
And anyway. when I saw that.
my bag...

54
00:05:49.200 --> 00:05:55.480
All you all right. miss?
-Yes. of course I'm all right.

55
00:05:55.640 --> 00:05:59.680
I'm perfectly all right.
Why? Don't I look all right?

56
00:05:59.800 --> 00:06:02.920
You look just fine. It's just...

57
00:06:03.080 --> 00:06:08.920
that when you were in here before...
-Before? What do you mean before?

58
00:06:09.080 --> 00:06:13.760
I've never been in here before.
-You were in here a few minutes ago.

59
00:06:13.920 --> 00:06:18.800
Me? I've never been in here before.

60
00:06:18.960 --> 00:06:21.080
What's the matter with 
this place anyway?

61
00:06:21.240 --> 00:06:24.480
Somebody keeps taking my bag. Somebody
says I keep asking about the bus...

62
00:06:24.640 --> 00:06:29.720
and you say I've been in here before.
-Easy. It's going to be all right.

63
00:06:29.880 --> 00:06:34.320
Of course it's going to be all right.
Nothing wrong to begin with.

64
00:06:34.480 --> 00:06:42.160
The only thing wrong with you people
is you need some sleep or something.

65
00:06:46.880 --> 00:06:52.600
Let me get you a cold cloth. honey.
I don't think you're well.

66
00:06:57.160 --> 00:07:02.480
No. I don't need that.
No. I'll be all right.

67
00:07:02.840 --> 00:07:10.920
I must be overtired
but I'll be all right.

68
00:07:53.920 --> 00:07:55.920
Excuse me.
-Yes?

69
00:07:56.080 --> 00:08:00.120
I wonder if you saw someone
sitting in my seat.

70
00:08:00.280 --> 00:08:04.920
I don't thinks so. miss.
I wasn't looking very close.

71
00:08:05.080 --> 00:08:08.280
What's the trouble?
-No. no trouble.

72
00:08:08.440 --> 00:08:11.240
I just thought I saw 
somebody I knew.

73
00:08:11.400 --> 00:08:14.720
In here?
-Thank you.

74
00:08:14.880 --> 00:08:18.160
I'm sorry to have disturbed you.

75
00:08:45.680 --> 00:08:47.960
What's the matter with me?

76
00:08:48.120 --> 00:08:52.480
What on earth is the matter with me?
What's happening?

77
00:08:52.640 --> 00:08:57.360
Delusions. that's what they are.

78
00:08:57.520 --> 00:09:02.800
I must be sick.
I must be running a fever.

79
00:09:02.960 --> 00:09:10.560
I'm not even warm.
I don't have any fever.

80
00:09:17.120 --> 00:09:22.240
Excuse me. miss.
-Yes. what is it?

81
00:09:22.400 --> 00:09:27.160
Your bag. I think you dropped it.
-Oh. thank you.

82
00:09:27.320 --> 00:09:34.280
The bus is late. isn't it?
-Yes. over a half an hour late.

83
00:09:34.480 --> 00:09:37.800
You do mean the bus to Cortland?
-That's the one.

84
00:09:37.960 --> 00:09:40.600
I was supposed to be in Syracuse 
tonight by 10:00.

85
00:09:40.760 --> 00:09:43.680
The planes were all grounded 
so I took a cab from Binghamton.

86
00:09:43.840 --> 00:09:47.360
It skidded into a tree
a few miles outside of here.

87
00:09:47.520 --> 00:09:52.600
I had to walk into town to get here.

88
00:09:55.520 --> 00:09:59.880
Forgive me. you're not ill. are you?

89
00:10:00.840 --> 00:10:06.400
I really don't know 
what's wrong with me.

90
00:10:06.720 --> 00:10:10.960
Is there something I can do?
-Well. I don't know.

91
00:10:11.120 --> 00:10:16.240
It's just that all sorts of queer 
things have been happening to me.

92
00:10:16.400 --> 00:10:20.600
I've been seeing things.
-Seeing things?

93
00:10:20.760 --> 00:10:24.160
What sort of things?

94
00:10:25.120 --> 00:10:26.840
I'm not sure I should tell you.

95
00:10:27.000 --> 00:10:30.000
You'd probably want to move
to another part of the room.

96
00:10:30.160 --> 00:10:33.760
Or call the police or an ambulance.

97
00:10:33.920 --> 00:10:36.640
Well. why don't you tell me.
Maybe I can help.

98
00:10:36.800 --> 00:10:42.200
My name is Paul Grinstead.
I'm from Binghamton.

99
00:10:42.360 --> 00:10:45.760
How do you do?
I'm Millicent Barnes.

100
00:10:45.920 --> 00:10:48.360
At least I was Millicent Barnes.

101
00:10:48.520 --> 00:10:52.240
I'm a private secretary.
I quit my job here on Thursday.

102
00:10:52.400 --> 00:10:58.160
And I've got another job in Buffalo.
That's where I'm going tonight.

103
00:10:58.760 --> 00:11:03.360
Everybody keeps telling me
that I've been here before.

104
00:11:03.520 --> 00:11:07.800
That man who takes the tickets. he 
says I keep asking about the bus.

105
00:11:07.960 --> 00:11:11.560
The woman in the powder room says 
I've been there before. and I haven't.

106
00:11:11.720 --> 00:11:17.960
And my bag here... My bag!
-There it is.

107
00:11:18.120 --> 00:11:22.960
Thank god. For a minute I thought 
it was starting all over again.

108
00:11:23.120 --> 00:11:26.200
That man said I checked it 
and I hadn't.

109
00:11:26.360 --> 00:11:29.720
But there was a bag. 
almost identical to mine.

110
00:11:29.880 --> 00:11:33.960
And then when I came out of the
powder room it wasn't there.

111
00:11:34.120 --> 00:11:37.600
Go on.

112
00:11:37.760 --> 00:11:41.800
It sounds very strange but...

113
00:11:41.960 --> 00:11:46.640
when I came out  of the powder room.
I looked in the mirror...

114
00:11:46.800 --> 00:11:50.200
and I could see the whole 
waiting room. In the mirror.

115
00:11:50.360 --> 00:11:54.560
And I...

116
00:11:56.040 --> 00:12:00.120
What did you see. Ms Barnes?

117
00:12:02.040 --> 00:12:08.440
I saw myself sitting right 
here on this bench.

118
00:12:09.160 --> 00:12:11.800
It's delusions.
-Yes.

119
00:12:11.960 --> 00:12:15.440
Yes. that's what it must be.
Delusions. some sort of delusions.

120
00:12:15.600 --> 00:12:22.080
But I'm not sick.
I'm not running a fever.

121
00:12:22.240 --> 00:12:26.480
But it's not just seeing things 
that don't exist.

122
00:12:26.640 --> 00:12:31.440
Why did that man and that woman say
that they had seen me before?

123
00:12:31.600 --> 00:12:37.160
I don't know.
This one's tough to figure out.

124
00:12:37.320 --> 00:12:42.240
What's happening to me? What's wrong?
I'm not some sort of kook.

125
00:12:42.400 --> 00:12:46.960
I've never had any trouble like this.
I mean. trouble with my mind.

126
00:12:47.120 --> 00:12:50.800
Of course you haven't.
There's an explanation some place.

127
00:12:50.960 --> 00:12:56.720
There's a reason. Maybe...
-Maybe what?

128
00:12:56.880 --> 00:13:00.600
Maybe there's someone here who 
resembles you. That could be it.

129
00:13:00.760 --> 00:13:05.600
Or maybe someone is playing some 
kind of a joke or something.

130
00:13:05.760 --> 00:13:08.920
Is that possible?

131
00:13:09.080 --> 00:13:15.400
That's too fantastic. And that 
doesn't explain about the bag.

132
00:13:15.560 --> 00:13:21.280
And anyway. if there is 
such a person. where is she?

133
00:13:23.800 --> 00:13:30.160
Bus to Cortland.
Syracuse. Buffalo. now arriving.

134
00:13:30.320 --> 00:13:35.920
Let me take that. Looks heavy.
-Thank you. You're very kind.

135
00:13:36.080 --> 00:13:40.240
No. you are more than just kind.

136
00:13:40.400 --> 00:13:44.040
We better get on the bus.

137
00:13:44.760 --> 00:13:48.680
I'll take your bag.
-All right.

138
00:13:58.000 --> 00:14:04.600
Ms Barnes! Millicent. 
What's the matter? Wait a minute.

139
00:14:16.440 --> 00:14:19.680
On our way.
You and the lady coming or aren't?

140
00:14:19.840 --> 00:14:25.080
No. we'll wait for the next one.
-That's due at 7:00 in the morning.

141
00:14:25.240 --> 00:14:29.960
You've got a long wait.
-That's all right.

142
00:14:30.120 --> 00:14:32.080
I'm shutting off some 
of these lights.

143
00:14:32.240 --> 00:14:34.960
'When not in use. 
turn off the juice.'

144
00:14:35.120 --> 00:14:40.080
That's what I always say.
-I best be getting home.

145
00:14:40.240 --> 00:14:45.040
I sure hope she feels better.
-Thank you. You've been very nice.

146
00:14:45.200 --> 00:14:51.400
It's all right. But I'd say she
needed some looking after.

147
00:14:51.560 --> 00:14:55.640
You know what I mean.

148
00:15:06.640 --> 00:15:10.240
You feeling better?

149
00:15:12.280 --> 00:15:14.600
The bus.
-It had to leave.

150
00:15:14.760 --> 00:15:18.800
There'll be another before too long.
-You didn't get on.

151
00:15:18.960 --> 00:15:23.960
I'm this late already. A few more
hours won't make any difference.

152
00:15:27.400 --> 00:15:31.560
I've been thinking about something.

153
00:15:32.960 --> 00:15:35.760
It's very odd. but...

154
00:15:35.920 --> 00:15:38.560
I've been remembering.

155
00:15:38.720 --> 00:15:41.840
Remembering what?

156
00:15:42.000 --> 00:15:50.440
About something I read or 
heard about a long time ago.

157
00:15:53.040 --> 00:15:56.960
About different planes of existence.

158
00:15:57.120 --> 00:16:01.040
About two parallel worlds.

159
00:16:01.200 --> 00:16:05.240
That exist side by side.

160
00:16:05.880 --> 00:16:10.560
And each of us has a 
counterpart in this world.

161
00:16:10.720 --> 00:16:16.720
And sometimes through some freak.
through something unexplainable...

162
00:16:16.880 --> 00:16:21.120
This counterpart.
after the two worlds converge...

163
00:16:21.280 --> 00:16:24.320
Comes into our world and
in order to survive...

164
00:16:24.480 --> 00:16:30.000
It has to take over.
-Take over?

165
00:16:30.160 --> 00:16:36.520
Replace us.
Move us out so that it can live.

166
00:16:36.920 --> 00:16:40.360
That's a little metaphysical for me.

167
00:16:40.520 --> 00:16:44.600
I remember reading it somewhere.

168
00:16:44.760 --> 00:16:49.080
Each of us has a twin 
in this other world.

169
00:16:49.240 --> 00:16:52.880
An identical twin.

170
00:16:53.040 --> 00:16:55.920
Maybe that woman I saw...

171
00:16:56.080 --> 00:17:00.160
Millicent. there has to be
another explanation.

172
00:17:00.320 --> 00:17:04.480
One that comes with more reason.

173
00:17:04.640 --> 00:17:07.480
I can't explain it.

174
00:17:07.640 --> 00:17:11.000
But I know that's what's happened.

175
00:17:11.160 --> 00:17:15.200
This other woman. my counterpart...

176
00:17:15.360 --> 00:17:20.680
Forget about it. please.
Don't think about it.

177
00:17:22.360 --> 00:17:27.720
I just thought of something. I've got
a good friend who lives in Tully.

178
00:17:27.880 --> 00:17:31.000
I'll call him. Maybe he'll 
bring his car down here for us.

179
00:17:31.160 --> 00:17:36.760
He might even drive us 
into Syracuse.

180
00:17:38.440 --> 00:17:44.000
All right. Millicent?
Shall I call my friend?

181
00:17:57.720 --> 00:18:03.240
I'll tell you what I think. I'd say
she's got a leak in her attic.

182
00:18:03.400 --> 00:18:09.360
Parallel planes.
Counterparts from another life.

183
00:18:09.640 --> 00:18:13.960
You got a thing about sick people?
Is that it?

184
00:18:14.120 --> 00:18:18.360
Poor. poor kid.
I don't know what's going to happen.

185
00:18:18.520 --> 00:18:24.000
Go call your friend.
Your friend in Tully with the car.

186
00:18:24.160 --> 00:18:26.960
I don't have any friend in Tully.

187
00:18:27.120 --> 00:18:30.480
She needs help. medical help.

188
00:18:30.640 --> 00:18:34.600
I figured it would be easier this way.

189
00:18:34.760 --> 00:18:37.440
Poor kid.

190
00:18:37.600 --> 00:18:40.560
Can I use it?
-Go ahead.

191
00:18:40.720 --> 00:18:44.800
Who're you going to call?
-The police. I guess.

192
00:18:44.960 --> 00:18:47.120
They're the ones that could help us.

193
00:18:47.280 --> 00:18:50.440
To tell you the truth. she
kind of gives me the willies.

194
00:18:50.600 --> 00:18:55.240
I'd as leave she got 
outta here somehow.

195
00:19:14.120 --> 00:19:17.440
Where are you?

196
00:19:21.920 --> 00:19:25.400
Where did you go?

197
00:19:25.640 --> 00:19:29.480
What do you want?

198
00:19:29.840 --> 00:19:34.280
Where are you?
-Millicent.

199
00:19:34.440 --> 00:19:38.360
Are you all right?

200
00:19:38.520 --> 00:19:44.360
Yes.
I'm all right.

201
00:19:45.840 --> 00:19:51.760
How about getting some fresh air?
-All right.

202
00:20:50.480 --> 00:20:53.680
Did you get her off all right?
-Yeah.

203
00:20:53.840 --> 00:20:56.520
They're gonna take her to the 
hospital for observation.

204
00:20:56.680 --> 00:21:01.600
What was she talking about?
Something about another life.

205
00:21:01.760 --> 00:21:06.720
I don't know. 
That's part of her illness. I guess.

206
00:21:08.120 --> 00:21:13.240
You said the next bus is at 7:00?
-You got about 4.5 hours. pal.

207
00:21:13.400 --> 00:21:18.960
You can take a snooze on that bench.
You'll be all alone. no noise at all.

208
00:21:19.120 --> 00:21:22.160
This place is like a tomb 
between night and morning.

209
00:21:22.280 --> 00:21:26.720
Maybe I will get some sleep.

210
00:22:04.400 --> 00:22:07.280
Hey.

211
00:22:14.800 --> 00:22:17.520
Hey!

212
00:22:36.440 --> 00:22:40.880
Hey. where are you?

213
00:22:43.240 --> 00:22:47.320
Obscure and metaphysical explanation
to cover a phenomena.

214
00:22:47.480 --> 00:22:52.800
Reasons to explain away that.
which can not be explained.

215
00:22:52.960 --> 00:22:56.400
Call it parallel planes 
or just insanity.

216
00:22:56.560 --> 00:23:03.760
Whatever it is. you find it
in the Twilight Zone.

217
00:23:04.960 --> 00:23:10.960
English Subtitles by
B. Cornelis - Pandorafilm - Heerlenn

